Greetings All! Today I was so very fortunate to host a “Paint and Juice: Girls Empowerment Session” at my former elementary/middle school. To be an alumnus of this most optional school is one thing, but to be able to come back and touch the souls of the youth who attend my former school is another. I truly enjoyed expressing to them how they are already beautiful black queens, the importance of getting a college education, and what it takes to get to this platform. I appreciate the love and support from Ms. Morton for giving me the opportunity to give back to these amazing girls and I hope I was able to inspire them all. 

Signed, 

Thee 71st Miss Mississippi Valley State University Elect💚🤍

Dear friends,

The moment we've all been waiting for is finally here! I am thrilled to invite you to witness a spectacular event, unlike any other – my Coronation! 

Prepare to be dazzled as I step into a new chapter of my life, adorned in regal attire and surrounded by the enchanting aura of royalty. Together, let's celebrate this remarkable occasion, filled with grace, elegance, and unparalleled grandeur.

📅 Date: October 12, 2023 
🕕 Time: 7:00 p.m. 
📍 Venue: R.W. Harrison Complex (New Gym)
👚 Attire: Formal or Semi- Formal

"Life's journey becomes lighter when you travel with a strong support system, for in their embrace, challenges are surmountable and joys are multiplied.”

Now that I am finally settling down, I can formally introduce myself , no longer as the elect but the OFFICIAL 71st Miss Mississippi Valley State University 💚

This achievement is not just mine, but a testament to the unwavering support, love, and encouragement I have received from my amazing family, cherished friends, incredible sisters, and my loving boyfriend. ❤️

To my family, you have been my rock and my biggest cheerleaders. Your belief in me has given me the strength to reach for the stars, and for that, I am endlessly thankful.

To my friends, your constant encouragement and laughter have made every step of this journey memorable. Each of you holds a special place in my heart, and I am grateful for the beautiful friendships we share.

To my sisters, you are my source of inspiration. Your support has been a guiding light, reminding me of the power of unity and sisterhood. Together, we are unstoppable.

And to my boyfriend, your love has been one of my greatest motivations. Your belief in my dreams has fueled my determination, and I am blessed to have you by my side.

This crown is a symbol of our collective strength, love, and unity. I am deeply touched by all the support I have received, and I promise to wear this crown with pride, humility, and the knowledge that it represents the incredible community that surrounds me.

As I wear the this crown with strength and dignity, I ask nothing more but for you to put your trust in me as I pave the way for success.

Thank you, everyone, for being a part of this beautiful journey. Here's to celebrating the power of support, friendship, and love! 

Signed, THEE 71st👑
